## Security Considerations

### Authentication & Authorization

- JWT tokens stored in httpOnly cookies (not localStorage)
- Token refresh mechanism with sliding expiration
- Rate limiting on authentication endpoints (5 attempts per 15 minutes)
- Password requirements: minimum 8 characters, uppercase, number, special character
- OAuth integration with Google, Discord, Steam

### Data Protection

- All API communication over HTTPS
- Content Security Policy headers to prevent XSS
- Input sanitization for user-generated content
- SQL injection prevention via parameterized queries
- CSRF protection for state-changing operations

### WebSocket Security

- Authentication required before establishing connection
- Message validation and sanitization
- Rate limiting on message sending
- Connection timeout after inactivity
- Origin validation

### Privacy

- User data anonymization in analytics
- GDPR compliance with data export/deletion
- Cookie consent management
- Privacy-compliant tracking with user consent
- Secure session management

